1C pass 1S pass 2S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 2, nRot: 0, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "3187dd05d014520d5eeb9ffd8e8ee626e6cdc8bd8cb3ce8ddc6b0d7ad1f510e9"]
[Category "Basic Bidding"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "basic_bidding/minor_suit_openings"]
[Student "S"]
{You have plenty good support to raise partner's \C suit. But your first priority is to show a 4-card Major suit if you have one. You do, so you respond 1\S. Partner raises you to 2\S.  

Are you tempted to take partner back to \Cs since you have such good support? Don't be. Partner has 4 \Ss, but he might have only 3 \Cs.

Are you tempted to bid 3\S since partner raised you? Don't be. He showed a minimum hand with his single raise and you only have 9 points. Just pass.}

